I'm pretty sure the post I wrote on Firehouse Subs' Facebook page got deleted by their admin, so I'll just write it here: Just had the worst sandwich at the Lafayette location. For starters, the bag that my sandwich came in had barbecue sauce smeared on it, which ended up smearing all over me before I realized. The sandwich I ordered didn't even have barbecue sauce, so obviously from a different order. When I opened the box the sandwich was a mess. The cheese was a huge glob, and it looked like the dressing was just slopped on. It was an unrecognizable mess, which was hard to eat, and unappetizing. It looked like whomever made it was in a hurry, and it wasn't busy when I went in.  I only ate half the sandwich and I got instant intestinal distress. Not going back. Very disappointed.
